					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Silver's Paladin guide 1-40</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:usuck007@yahoo.com">Chris Coleman</a> | 
		            8/12/2002 11:41:28 AM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Alright, this is (in my opinion) the easiest way to hit 40 as a paladin.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
First, if you chose to be a human paladin like I did get out of the qeynos hills as quickly as you can.  This area sux compared to the freeport newbie zone.  The main reason for this is the lack of people.  In the freeport area you can almost always find a group, and there are enough roaming mobs to keep you busy soloing while waiting on an opening in the constant groups at the orc camps.<BR>
<BR>
Ok, onto the guide:<BR>
<BR>
1-5: For the first five levels follow the standard rat and snake killing method of leveling right outside the gates of freeport.  this will take no time since Verant sped up the leveling process for levels 1-10.  Loot everything you can untill you can not carry anymore, and save all of the cash.  use a rusty weapon off of one of the decaying skellies roaming around during the night. <BR>
<BR>
6-12: As soon as you hit lvl 5 head to East Commons and get on the waiting list for one of the orc camps. This is one of the most fun camping areas in the game.  This is just because it is the first real grouping you will get a chance to do.  You can learn alot here and get a feel for the role of the paladin.  Make sure to buy your spells as soon as you hit lvl 9 so you can help the group a little more.  The rest of the group will love you at this point because of all the things you can do, and because the difference between you and the warriors is very small. Stay here until the orcs turn green to you and then head to Nro.<BR>
<BR>
13-17: Get into one of the 3 derv groups and ask the rest of the group if you can loot all the dervish cutthroat rings.  You will need these if you are planning on getting Ro Armor later in the game.  Since this armor isnt very good for the level you need to be to get it I would advise against it, but many people like to do it just for fun.  You will need the rings to increase your Ro faction, and you can gain some exp and cash by turning them in to the orc in Sro on the norther side of the desert part of the zone.  Stay in Nro until you lvl 17 or 18.  At this point you should have a bronze weapon from one of the dervs, or if you decided to spend some money you could probably pick up a fine steel or velium weapon. I would suggest you just use the bronze &quot;FREE&quot; weapon you can loot from the dervs. <BR>
<BR>
17-22:  Head to the Oasis as soon as you hit 17 and get into a Highway group.  This zone is fun, and can be dangerous due to the Sandgiants that pop up, or the people that train the spectres to the HW.  Many people say you should hunt the crocs here, but I thought they were way too boring, and the loot absolutly sucked.  When you here that Lockjaw has spawned find out who is killing him and see if you can loot the vest that drops. Most of the time you can get it for free or for under 20pp.  This vest will serve you until you buy a full suit of bronze armor(piece by piece, do not wait until you can buy the whole thing.) Once you hit 22, make sure you have all of your spells, a full suit of what ever armor you can buy, and catch a port or boat to ButcherBlock and then head to unrest.<BR>
<BR>
22-30:  Stay in unrest!  I can not tell you how good this zone is.  You get a 25% bonus here, and can hunt here even after lvl 30 for great experience.  I suggest leaving it at 30 to break up the boredom.  While you are here, beware of trains!!!.  Do not camp the entryway of this zone, head to the gazeebo, backwall or westwall of the zone to pull to.  The entryway is trained about every 5 min in unrest and will wipe out your entire group until you are close to 30.  when you get closer to 30 you can move in doors to hold the round room, or head downstairs with a GOOD group to kill werebats and hags.  At 30 upgrade your armor as best you can and buy a decent weapon. I suggest 2hs because your epic is 2hs, but many people like to use a shield(your choice).  Head back to the Freeport area and get in a group in SolA - A dungeon in the lavastorm Mountains.  This area will be your home for the next 6 levels.  Sol A has great loot, and fast exp.  If you want to break up the boredom here head over to najena (also off of Lavastorm) to group here.  Also great loot, but less exp.  Once you hit 36 you have a couple of choices.<BR>
<BR>
36-40:  I would suggest you head to Uguk to get your Goulbane.  The exp here will be awful at 36, but once you get the goulbane you can head down to Lguk Deadside to group and wipe the floor with your goulbane. OR<BR>
<BR>
Head to Iceclad and get in a cougar group for a couple of levels trying to get some Cougar claw Earrings.  These are basically the same as orcfang earrings, but with a mana preservation effect that is handy. OR-<BR>
<BR>
Head to Crystal Caverns for great Loot, Great Exp and A great time.  This is my personal favorite for this level range.  It can sometimes take awhile to get in a group, but when you do you can gain exp faster than you can imagine, and the loot that drops here is great!<BR>
<BR>
Other options for various levels to break up the boredom and to see some new sites:<BR>
<BR>
15-25: Runneyeye(fun zone, slow exp and somewhat dangerous, but decent loot), West Commons(Boring but available), CrushBone(GO HERE when you are bored.  FUN ZONE and you can get a good shield off the trainer on the top of the hill.- Beware the trains- If you were not a paladin I would suggest this over Unrest)<BR>
<BR>
25-30: UGuk( I thought this place was boring, but you can get good exp here as well as you GB and also a great shield off of the giant heart spider), Lower Runneyeye (bottom floor of runnyeye has some great armor drops that you can use instead of buying Fine Steel)<BR>
<BR>
30-35: Unrest again(basement only!  Great experience again), Mistmoore(Awesome zone if you are brave, decent loot)<BR>
<BR>
35-40: Mistmoore(Less dangerous at this level), Splitpaw( I hate this zone, but a good mask drops here for us Humans!  Splitpaw Hide Mask = Light source!)<BR>
<BR>
As you can see, I am big on hunting in dungeons because the experience is usually better, and it is more exciting.  You will also note that I left Kunark out of this guide because I found that most of that island is BORING!!!, But to be honest you can get some good experience in LOIO in the mid 20's, and some great loot in Frontier Mountains in you low 30's.  DL's is a good place at 39+ for exp, and Dalnir is good during you 30+ lvl range.  But I personally believe that you can get the best experience from the zones I listed above, and also have the most fun. I will not stay in a zone if it is boring, regardless of how good the experience is.<BR>
<BR>
P.S. Once you hit 40 try to get a group to go into the Tower of Frozen Shadow with you.  It is Like a beefed up unrest with Great experience, excitement, and awesome loot.<BR>
<BR>
Well, that is the guide.  Take it for what it is worth.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Silversam &lt;Steel and Honor&gt;<BR>
Paladin of the 40th<BR>
Saryrn Server
